<section class="introduction">
  <p><strong>Product layouts</strong> blend imagery, pricing, and calls-to-action so people can recognize what is being offered and what to do next. Thoughtful typography and link styling keep titles scannable, while button treatments make primary actions obvious even in dense grids.</p>
  <p>Use the patterns below as a toolkit: cards for quick browsing, lists for content-heavy catalogs, and detail views for deep decisions. Keep labels, tags, and helper text intentional so every product stays accessible and consistent with the wider documentation style.</p>
</section>


